        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"18948\">@Nehal Sharma</span>  When adding a new poll option, the entire modal jumps up, which I don't think is a good UX.  So, I propose:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix height of the modal based on screen height.</li>\n<li>Instead of scrolling the entire modal when the options overflow the modal container, we add scrolling only to the options part.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This will create an experience which is more like other modals here. Thoughts?</p>",
        "id": 1416163,
        "sender_full_name": "Aman (amanagr)",
        "timestamp": 1659776813
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sounds good to me, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"5140\">@Aman Agrawal (amanagr)</span>! Can you give examples of other modals which have scrollable elements within them?</p>",
